5 (2) "Public safety services" means law enforcement, firefighting, hospital, ambulance, or
6 emergency medical services offered to the general public.
7 (3) “Public services” means any of the following that are offered to the general public:
8 (a) county services and facilities;
9 (b)(a) educational services and facilities; or
10 (c)(b) hospital or emergency medical services and facilities.
11 (4) (a) "Qualified petitioner" means:
12 (A) FOR A PETITION RELATED TO A HOSPITAL DISTRICT, an owner of real property in a service LOCATED
13 WITHIN THE HOSPITAL district:
14 (i) whose property is more quickly REASONABLY accessible to public safety services or public
15 services headquartered in the county seat or closest city, town, resort community, resort area, or resort area
16 district of an adjoining county than to public safety services or public services headquartered in the county seat
17 or closest city, town, resort community, resort area, or resort area district of the county in which the owner's
18 property is located, or
19 (ii) from whose property the owner has an inability to access public services from the county seat
20 or closest city, town, resort community, resort area, or resort area district of the county in which the owner’s
21 property is located;
22 (B) FOR A PETITION RELATED TO A SCHOOL DISTRICT, A PETITION DESCRIBED IN 20-6-105.
23 (b) For the purposes of [sections 1 through 8 ], a qualified petitioner includes a real property owner
24 that is a corporation, limited liability company, partnership, or trust regardless of the state of principal domicile.
25 (5) “Service district” means a hospital district created under Title 7, chapter 34, part 21, or a school
26 district created under Title 20, chapter 6.
27 (5) "SCHOOL DISTRICT" MEANS A SCHOOL DISTRICT CREATED UNDER TITLE 20, CHAPTER 6.
